Package: icewm
Version: 1.2.0
Revision: 3
GCC: 3.1
BuildDepends: libjpeg, libpng, libtiff, netpbm, audiofile, esound, glib, gtk+, orbit, giflib, imlib, gnome-libs-dev
Depends: gnome-libs
Source: mirror:sourceforge:%n/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 0972000f4f0569c34ff03c8db200d396 
SourceDirectory: %n-%v
Patch: %f.patch
UpdateConfigGuess: true
ConfigureParams: --with-docdir=%p/share/doc --disable-debug --disable-i18n --enable-nls --enable-guievents --with-gnome-menus --with-xpm --with-icesound=esd
Conflicts: icewm-basic
Replaces: icewm-basic
CompileScript: <<
 ./configure %c
 make SYS_LIBDIRS=-L%p/lib
<<
InstallScript: <<
 make install install-docs prefix=%i PREFIX=%i DOCDIR=%i/share/doc
<<
#
Description: Window manager with Windows, OS/2 and Motif themes
DescDetail: <<
icewm is a nice window manager designed for speed, usability and
consistency. It is able to emulate the look of Motif, OS/2, Windows
and allows to have a customizable look using pixmaps.
<<
DescPort: <<
Uses autoconf, but not automake. 

We don't use the Imlib support because of shared memory problems 
(compiler errors result if --with-imlib is passed to configure).

Sound is enabled but untested.

i18n support is disabled since configure expects langinfo.h which doesn't
exist on OS X.
<<
